# Passed to `docker run --env-file .env` for local dev, and also how this
# database deploys on Bzync Cloud itself — this tier has no managed/linked
# database service (mdb was removed; see the workspace root README.md), so
# this template deployed as its own app *is* the database. The platform
# DOES seed these as the project's real env vars on first deploy (see
# BZYNC_CLOUD) — but any value literally "changeme" is replaced with a
# generated random secret at seed time, never passed through as-is. See
# README.md for the values to copy into any other app that needs to
# connect (no automatic injection between apps here).

REDIS_VERSION=
REDIS_PASSWORD=changeme
